restaurant.name: Pizza Mercato
restaurant.description: Pizza Mercato serves up all kinds of pizza, pasta, and sandwiches.
restaurant.landmark: Corner of Mercer & Waverly Place (1 block west of Broadway)

restaurant.name: The Cottage
restaurant.description: Chinese food, cheap and satisfying. Pick for delivery any number of your favorites from the menu: wontons, chicken, lo mein, etc. What more could you want (except more Chinese food)?If paying by credit card, customer is required to present card at time of delivery.

restaurant.name: Third Ave Blue 9 Burger
restaurant.description: If you want some quality fast-food burgers, head over to Blue 9. Also try their fresh fries and shakes. It's cheap and you won't be disappointed.
restaurant.cuisines: Burgers, Convenience Items, Juice Bar, Beer

restaurant.name: Duke's (Gramercy)
restaurant.description: Duke's is a sports bar, but it's also a restaurant that specializes in classic American food. Particularly known is its Southern comfort food, such as barbeque.

restaurant.name: Big Daddy's Diner
restaurant.description: Opened in 2005, Big Daddy's is a super-cool and groovy hip diner, serving breakfast, lunch, dinner and late-night munchies 7 days a week. From all the diner classics to the reinvented, Big Daddy's has something for everyone.Open 24 Hours Fridays and Saturdays Credit Card Orders Only After Midnight

restaurant.name: Ray's Gourmet Market
restaurant.description: Ray's is a combination deli/pizzeria/ice-creamery. Order anything from pizza, soft drinks, bagels, and salads.

restaurant.name: The Village Pourhouse
restaurant.description: This well-known sports bar also serves classic American fare such as burgers, sandwiches, and wings.

restaurant.name: Village Farm & Grocery (open 24/7)
restaurant.description: Village Farm and Grocery is a convenient grocery store, open 24/7, that delivers produce, sandwiches, ice creams, beverages, and household items.Please allow Three HOURS for delivery for any orders ABOVE 35th or BELOW BROOME Street. For orders in Brooklyn, please allow up to Four (4) HOURS for delivery. CREDIT CARD MUST BE PRESENT AT THE TIME OF DELIVERY. Please note that if you are not available to receive the order, Village Farm will charge a fee to your Credit Card no greater than 15% of the total amount.

restaurant.name: Amici
restaurant.description: Amici is a small pizzeria that serves a wide range of traditional pizzas and specialty pizzas.

restaurant.name: S'MAC
restaurant.description: Weekend Deliveries May Take About an Hour and a Half to Deliver.

restaurant.name: Bocca
restaurant.description: Bocca is an upscale Italian trattoria. Dishes here are authentic Italian, with many meat, seafood, pasta, and vegetable dishes.

restaurant.name: 99 Miles to Philly
restaurant.description: 99 Miles to Philly is a small restaurant in the Village that specializes in sandwiches--namely, the Philly cheese steak

restaurant.name: Grand Sichuan
restaurant.description: Grand Sichuan is a classic Chinese restaurant located on St. Mark's Place.

restaurant.name: Sunburst Espresso Bar
restaurant.description: Sunburst Espresso Bar is just what you'd expect with a name like that: friendly, casual, and perfect for some good food to start your day.

restaurant.name: Little Atlas Cafe
restaurant.description: Little Atlas offers sandwiches, vegetarian options, and lots of vegan items on their menu as well. Try one of their offerings from the coffee bar along with your lunch or dinner for a quick pick-me-up.

restaurant.name: Bite
restaurant.description: Bite may be cheap, but that doesn't mean you have to sacrifice either taste or choice. With a wide selection of menu items, you can choose for delivery any number of popular soups, salads, sandwiches, and more. With distinctive blends of spices and fusions, you can be sure your sandwich will have its own creative spin.

restaurant.name: Tanti Baci Caffe
restaurant.description: Tanti Baci Caffé is one of New York Citys most romantic, authentic Italian restaurants. Since 1992, Tanti Baci Caffe has been serving New Yorkers with original Southern and Northern recipes from the old Italian country using all natural and imported ingredients. No wonder customers who try Tanti Baci order again and again!

restaurant.name: Klong Thai
restaurant.description: Klong Thai serves up Thai favorites, as well as specialty dishes.

restaurant.name: Cafe Medina
restaurant.description: Cafe Medina is a good place to order from for its wide selection of sandwiches, flavorful paninis, and eclectic range of soups. If you want a filling sandwich, soup, or salad for a reasonable price, Cafe Medina is a good bet.

restaurant.name: Burger Creations
restaurant.description: Our burgers and specialty sandwiches are carefully prepared from the very best ingredients that are delivered to us daily. Through our commitment to quality and our renowned original recipes, we strive to transform your traditional burger into a premium culinary experience. Enjoy!

restaurant.name: Ponty Bistro
restaurant.description: Ponty Bistro serves a fusion of Senegalese and French food. Try traditional French and African appetizers and entrees, as well as sandwiches on fresh baguettes.

restaurant.name: Ray's Pizza & Bagel Cafe
restaurant.description: Ray's Pizza & Bagel Cafe is a counter service deli and pizzeria located on St. Mark's place.

restaurant.name: Havana Central (Union Square)
restaurant.description: Havana Central serves traditional Cuban dishes that are sure to satisfy your craving for rice, chicken, soups, and all your favorites.

restaurant.name: Coffee Shop
restaurant.description: The Coffee Shop is a nondescript little Brazilian bar/restaurant tucked away in Union Square. Although there's a lounge and bar, this eatery is known for its traditional Brazilian dishes.

restaurant.name: Stand 4
restaurant.description: Stand is known for its burgers, but also offers tons of American favorites: original and creative salads, fries, and shakes are the go-tos here.

restaurant.name: Insomnia Cookies
restaurant.description: Insomnia Cookies is here to serve all of your late-night, sweet-tooth needs. Got a hankering for some hot, fresh-out-of-the-oven cookies at 11PM? Insomnia has got you covered with eleven cookie varieties and brownies, too!Please note: estimated delivery time is 30-45 minutes. Inclement weather may increase the delivery time.

restaurant.name: Stromboli Pizzeria
restaurant.description: Stromboli pizzeria is a neighborhood pizza joint that serves up all kinds of pizza slices.

restaurant.name: Plump Asian Cuisine
restaurant.description: Plump Dumpling is a cute little Asian eatery that serves Chinese, Thai, and Vietnamese favorites and, of course, dumplings.

restaurant.name: Bully's
restaurant.description: Bully's is one of your classic American diners in the best tradition: fast food, all your favorites, and a wide selection of foods that are especially great for a no-fuss, satisfying breakfast, lunch, or dinner.

restaurant.name: Thai Terminal
restaurant.description: Thai Terminal is a great bet for basic, satisfying Thai food. All your favorites are here, at affordable prices.

restaurant.name: Tahini
restaurant.description: Tahini is a modern, counter-serve Middle Eastern restaurant in the Village.

restaurant.name: Delion
restaurant.description: Delion is a bodega, your friendly neighborhood bodega, that marries chicken parm sandwiches and liter bottles of soda under one roof. Half deli, half convenience store, it's open 24/7.

restaurant.name: Friend House
restaurant.description: Friend house is your, well, friendly neighborhood sushi bar. Serving up all the sushi, hand rolls, dumplings, dim sum, noodles, chicken, pork, and Thai food you could ever want, Friend House has got your Asian craving covered.

restaurant.name: Petite Abeille
restaurant.description: Get acquainted with fine Belgian cuisine at an affordable price by ordering a meal from Petite Abeille. "Petite Abeille" ("little bee"), which gets its name from a popular Belgian children's book of the 1970s, has been awarded praise for its hot chocolate, Belgian waffles, and Moules-frites (mussels with fries). Their delivery menu comes complete with Belgian breakfast, lunch, dinner & dessert options.

restaurant.name: Pie by the Pound
restaurant.description: Pie by the Pound serves up a wide array of oblong, very thin-crust pizzas.

restaurant.name: Shima
restaurant.description: Shima is a basic neighborhood sushi restaurant, that serves classics as well as specialty rolls.

restaurant.name: Spot Dessert Bar
restaurant.description: Spot Dessert Bar is a small, low-key dessert bar that serves high-end desserts: gourmet cupcakes, dessert tapas, and ice cream and sorbet with different toppings. There's a Japanese fusion angle to the food, which offers ingredients like green tea and rice cake. The tapas menu changes with each season.

restaurant.name: Red House
restaurant.description: Each NY neighborhood has its own sushi joint, and Red House could be yours! You can't go wrong with all your favorite Chinese dishes on the menu.

restaurant.name: The City Tavern
restaurant.description: The City Tavern specializes in American Traditional comfort food, including pasta, sandwiches, hamburgers, and salads.

restaurant.name: Zabb City
restaurant.description: Zapp City specializes in Thai classics as well as house creations: Thai and fusion appetizers, curries, salads, noodles, and sauteed entrees with a wide variety of sauces.

restaurant.name: Maoz Vegetarian
restaurant.description: This Dutch vegetarian chain has some of the best falafel in NY. It specializes in tasty falafel on fresh pita, and salads.

restaurant.name: Paul's Burgers
restaurant.description: Order from Paul's if you want to get a wide selection of burgers at an affordable price.

restaurant.name: Dogmatic
restaurant.description: Dogmatic specializes in--you guessed it--sausage dogs. Order in a selection of specialty sausage dogs, as well as fries and handmade soda.

restaurant.name: 9 Edo Sushi & Grill
restaurant.description: A popular Village sushi joint, Edo Sushi provides all your favorite rolls, many house specialty rolls, and also a wide array of Japanese entrees.

restaurant.name: John's of 12th Street
restaurant.description: You should order from John's on 12th Street if you want straight-up, old school Italian food--pasta, chicken, seafood, salads, all with a Mediterranean flair.

restaurant.name: Piola
restaurant.description: Piola specializes in tasty, inexpensive thin-crust pizza, as well as other styles of pizza and Italian pasta, salad, and meat specialties.

restaurant.name: Zen Palate
restaurant.description: This Union Square restaurant emphasizes not only vegetarian cuisine, but a healthy approach to Asian food. For its use of only the healthiest ingredients and its delicious fare, Zen Palate was voted the best vegetarian restaurant in NYC by Vogue.

restaurant.name: Baoguette Cafe
restaurant.description: This East Village spot specializes in Vietnamese sandwiches and noodles. With affordable prices, their banh mi sandwiches and pho are must-try dishes.

restaurant.name: BBQ Pit (brought to you by Kool Bloo)
Kool Bloo
restaurant.description: Offering healthy and non-healthy options 24/7, this eatery features typical American fare. No matter what you are in the mood for, Kool Bloo has something for you.

restaurant.name: Ashiya Japanese
restaurant.description: Ashiya Japanese is your friendly neighborhood sushi joint. However, it also serves up a myriad of other Japanese goodies like yakitori, negimaki, tempura, and teriyaki.

restaurant.name: Nomad
restaurant.description: Nomad is a North African tapas bar and restaurant. Get any one of the traditional North African entrees, or any one of their sandwiches, which give a North African twist to American staples.

restaurant.name: BBQ Pit (brought to you by Kool Bloo)
Funayama Japanese Restaurant
restaurant.description: Order fresh sushi in the heart of Greenwich Village from Funayama Japanese Restaurant. In addition to sushi, the menu features cooked entrees, salads, soups, and plenty of Japanese appetizers.

City Harvest
restaurant.description:
Make a donation to City Harvest with a Delivery.com order! You can help those in need by choosing items from the City Harvest menu. The total cost of your order will be sent as a donation to City Harvest, and help in their efforts to feed NYC's hungry. Upon receipt of your donation, you will be sent an acknowledgment letter from City Harvest.
City Harvest, the world's first and New York City's only food rescue organization, connects good food that would otherwise go to waste with people struggling with hunger. This year they will rescue 28 million pounds of food, helping to feed more than 300,000 men, women and children each week.This order will go directly to City Harvest as a monetary donation. No food will be delivered to you.

restaurant.name: Liebe
restaurant.description: At Liebe the traditional Kati Roll is reincarnated as the Liebe Roll," wrapped with the freshest local ingredients and fused with aromatic spices. All menu items are prepared daily and made to order creating a healthy, fresh-tasting experience.

restaurant.name: Kosher Deluxe
restaurant.description: Under the strict supervision of Rabbi Amram Roth of Boro Park.

restaurant.name: Kosher Deluxe Catering
restaurant.description: Under the strict supervision of Rabbi Amram Roth of Boro Park.

restaurant.name: IL Forno Pizzeria
restaurant.description: Il Forno is a neighborhood pizza joint, that also specializes in many different kinds of sandwiches, as well as salads.

restaurant.name: Iggy's Pizzeria
restaurant.description: Iggy's is a solid neighborhood pizza joint. With an array of pizzas, pastas, and other Italian entrees you can't go wrong.

restaurant.name: Mamani
restaurant.description: 2/26 - Restaurant is out of fries for the night

restaurant.name: Pomodoro Ristorante & Pizzeria
restaurant.description: Lovers of vodka sauce: rejoice! Pomodoro is using their creamy vodka sauce on penne and on pizzas, too. Pomodoro also serves up appetizers, heros, Italian entrees, and salads. Still craving vodka sauce? You can order it here by the pint.
restaurant.landmark: Between Cleveland Place and Mulberry St.

restaurant.name: Empire Szechuan Village
restaurant.description: Empire Szechuan Village has established itself as a cornerstone of the Greenwich Village community since 1985 by providing excellent service and great food. They feature selections in both Chinese and Japanese cuisine and also have a vegetarian section on the menu.If you require eating utensils, please indicate so in the special instructions field located in the checkout screen.

restaurant.name: Bamboo House
restaurant.description: A NYC Chinese eatery that rises above the competition. Delivery food is noted to arrive on time and hot as well. Also the food is delicious but the price can't be beat.

restaurant.name: Silver Spurs
restaurant.description:
Silver Spurs, 'home of the world's greatest hamburger,' is serving them up by the dozen. Also try one of their imaginatively-named sandwiches, "appeteasers," salads, and omelets. If using a Credit Card to pay for your order:
Please indicate your tip in the special instructions. (Restaurant is unable to acquire tip upon point-of-delivery). Thank you for your cooperation.
In order to process your credit card, Silver Spurs requires that you provide your CVV code. The restaurant will be contacting you after you place your order to obtain this information.
Please note NO requests for substitutions will be honored

restaurant.name: Two Boots To Go-Go
restaurant.description: The "two boots" are Louisiana and Italy, and Two Boots to Go-Go is combining the cuisines of these regions on top of pizza pies. If you're craving Cajun food and pizza, order one of Two-Boots' specialty pies.

restaurant.name: Hollywood Diner
restaurant.description: Hollywood Diner is a true New York City diner, serving up enormous portions of food for hungry customers. The menu covers just about every option you could ask for, including dozens of omelettes, Belgian waffles, salads, sandwiches, pasta, roasts, and seafood.

restaurant.name: Mee Summer Palace
restaurant.description: Chinese restaurant where the food is hot and tasty. Many delicious noodle options that are perfect for lunch or dinner.

restaurant.name: Alberto's Pizza & Cheesesteak Factory
restaurant.cuisines: Philly Steaks, Sandwiches, Pizza, Fast Food

restaurant.name: Izumi Sushi
restaurant.description: Izumi Sushi features a wide selection of sushi and Japanese dishes. The restaurant is known to give fairly large portions.

restaurant.name: Ditch Plains
restaurant.description: This sleek restaurant features high-quality seafood shack fare and comfort classics with a twist. Definitely try some fish or steak dishes, but save room for dessert! Ditch Plains is serving up 'smores, deep fried mini candy bars, and their Ditch 'Wich ice cream sandwich to give your meal a sweet finale.

restaurant.name: Koo Sushi
restaurant.description: Koo Sushi is serving up simple and inexpensive Japanese food. Dozens of rolls--both classic and more unique--are available from this small Japanese eatery.

restaurant.name: Masamoto Japanese
restaurant.description: This Japanese restaurant offers an extensive menu, including hibachi, teriyaki, and dozens of sushi appetizers and entrees. NYU students receive a 10% discount when NYU student ID is presented.

restaurant.name: Hong Kong Noodle II
restaurant.description: Cheap, good and quick delivery service. This Murry Hill Chinese restaurant understands good food at low cost.

restaurant.name: Sariku
restaurant.description: Generous pieces of large chunky fish make diners claim this to be among the best of NY sushi restaurants. Other options on the menu are also equally fresh and delicious and all come at great prices.

restaurant.name: Eleven B
restaurant.landmark: Corner of 11th St. and Ave. B

restaurant.name: Cucina di Pesce
restaurant.description: Utensils must be requested with each order submitted for this merchant.

restaurant.name: Pinche Taqueria
restaurant.description: Pinche is a taqueria through-and-through. Here you'll find authentic Mexican food, like tacos and burritos, made using fresh ingredients and seafood, with fresh salsas and sauces made from scratch complementing each dish.

restaurant.name: Dallas BBQ
restaurant.description: From the homemade cole slaw and chili to the steak and shrimp, Dallas BBQ (New York's favorite rotisserie!) is sure to satisfy your cravings all-American favorites. Be sure to try one of their virgin pina coladas to add a tropical splash to your meal!

restaurant.name: Beyond Thai Kitchen
restaurant.description: For a wide variety of signature Thai dishes, check out Beyond Thai Kitchen. Their lunch specials are sure to bring some of the exotic to your afternoon; also check out noodle, rice, curry, and special dinner entrees.

restaurant.name: Isle Thai Home Cooking
restaurant.description: For classic Thai dishes--noodles, curries, and specialty Thai entrees--order from Isle Thai. The menu is full of Thai favorites, with plenty of appetizers and soups to start off your meal. Try one of Thai Isle's main plates for lunch, which come with a free starter!

restaurant.name: Chelsea Cottage Chinese Restaurant
restaurant.description: Chelsea Cottage Chinese Restaurant uses authentic ingredients to prepare a wide variety of Chinese favorites, from appetizers to noodle dishes, entrees, and more!

restaurant.name: Grand Sichuan
restaurant.description: Grand Sichuan is on a mission to raise New Yorkers' appreciation and awareness of high quality Chinese cuisine. The menu features a plethora of lunch specials, and it also includes many noodle dishes, classical Sichuan dishes, and even a section devoted to the latest dishes introduced by the restaurant.

restaurant.name: Baluchi's
restaurant.description: Baluchi's, one of Zagat's top rated Indian restaurants, offers a selection of traditional & regional Indian cuisines that are carefully prepared and presented by experienced chefs. Choose from a wide variety of Indian dishes and Tandoori breads to accompany your meal.

restaurant.name: Ritz Asia
restaurant.description: Asian Fusion takes center stage at Ritz Asia, where a combination of Japanese, Chinese, and Thai specialties are on the extensive menu. Order from a wide array of appetizers, dim sum, sushi, noodles, and gourmet entrees.

restaurant.name: Table 12 (brought to you by Kool Bloo)
The Organic Grill
restaurant.description: The Organic Grill is what the name implies: all vegetarian, mostly vegan, serving American fusion dishes that are all healthy.

restaurant.name: Happy Taco Burrito
restaurant.description: Quick Mexican--fast-food style--is what you'll find from this taco & burrito shop. Some uncommon combinations, like a jack cheese & eel quesadilla, are featured on the menu alongside a plethora of typical Mexican street food favorites.

restaurant.name: Pinche Taqueria
restaurant.description: Pinche is a taqueria through-and-through. Here you'll find authentic Mexican food, like tacos and burritos, made using fresh ingredients and seafood, with fresh salsas and sauces made from scratch complementing each dish.

restaurant.name: Dallas Jones BBQ
restaurant.description: Dallas Jones BBQ (not to be confused with the Dallas BBQ chain) is a family owned and operated barbecue joint. When it was first opened in 1984, Dallas Jones was the first delivery business for BBQ ribs. The restaurant's commitment to BBQ dishes with epicurean tastes has positioned Dallas Jones as a true original and neighborhood favorite.

restaurant.name: Num Pang Sandwich Shop
restaurant.description: Specializing in Cambodian and Vietnamese sandwiches, Num Pang is popular especially with NYU students for their diversity and low prices. This is one place that definitely helps the cause of NY's new favorite sandwich, the banh mi.

restaurant.name: Tara Thai
restaurant.description: Tara Thai is an unfussy, family-owned, hole in the wall Thai restaurant. You can find online all of your favorite Thai classics, from noodle dishes to spring rolls at affordable prices.

restaurant.name: Candela Candela
restaurant.description: Candela Candela combines authentic Cuban and Italian cuisine. Order online for a simple but delicious meal for lunch or dinner.

restaurant.name: Luigi's Pizza Catering
restaurant.description: Whether you're planning a small dinner party or a large formal event, let Luigi's alleviate the stress by handling all of your catering needs.

restaurant.name: In2010 Restaurant
restaurant.landmark: Bet. West 10 St. & Christopher St. off 6th Ave,

restaurant.name: Atlas Cafe & Bakery
restaurant.description: Atlas Cafe & Bakery is a friendly vegan and vegetarian eatery. You can find all sorts of sandwiches, crepes, pasta, and pastries with a vegan or vegetarian twist.

restaurant.name: Pinkberry
restaurant.description: All Pinkberrys great tasting products are made fresh with the highest quality ingredients and Pinkberrys signature tang. Our menu includes Original, Pomegranate, Chocolate, Mango, Coconut and Green Tea frozen yogurts*, daily cut fresh fruit and seasonal fresh fruit toppings, as well as creative and premium dry and liquid toppings. Pinkberry also now serves a Fresh Fruit Parfait in addition to our Original and Green Tea smoothies. Get your taste of Swirly Goodness. *Product offerings may vary by stores. Orders may take 30-45 minutes for delivery. Pinkberry Gift Cards cannot be used for Delivery.com.

restaurant.name: Dirty Bird To Go
restaurant.description: With mentions in the New York Times and Daily Candy, you know the chicken at this joint has to be good. Fill up on chicken-comfort favorites like fried chicken, rotisserie chicken, and chicken fingers, plus wraps, sides like mac 'n cheese and smashed potatoes & gravy, and Dirty Bird's "Freshly Baked Bad-Ass Cookies."

restaurant.name: Olympic Pita
restaurant.description: Olympic Pita is a Midtown West kosher staple. The restaurant serves many Israeli and Middle Eastern dishes as well as sushi platters under strict kosher supervision.
restaurant.cuisines: Glatt Kosher, Kosher, OU Kosher, Israeli

restaurant.name: Bleecker Street Pizza
restaurant.description: The Bleecker Street authentic Tuscan thin-crust pizza from a family recipe passed through the generations. Nonna Maria left her birthplace of Tuscany at age nineteen, bringing with her the family recipe for this delectable pizza. Experience the tantalizing aroma and sublime flavor of this real Italian specialty pizza in New York City! Winner, Best Pizza in New York via the Food Network, three years running.

restaurant.name: Wai Cafe
restaurant.description: Healthy, casual, and affordable, Wai Cafe serves unfussy food for breakfast, brunch, lunch, and dinner. The cuisine is a mix of Asian, Italian, and traditional American, all with a healthy twist.

restaurant.name: This Little Piggy Had Roast Beef
Focacceria Catering
restaurant.description: Focaccia sandwiches and pasta dishes form the center point of Focacceria's menu of Italian favorites. Choose one of their specialty catering pasta dishes for your next party or gathering!

restaurant.name: Boyd Thai
restaurant.description: Boyd Thai serves up authentic Thai food, including Pad Thai, curries, salads, and noodle dishes. Levels of spiciness can be adjusted according to the customer's taste buds!

restaurant.name: Calcutta Cuisine of India
restaurant.description: Calcutta Cuisine of India serves up a large assortment of Indian cuisine: tikka masala, curry, and tandoori dishes are some examples of the dishes here.

restaurant.name: Focacceria
restaurant.description: Focaccia sandwiches and pasta dishes form the center point of Focacceria's menu of Italian favorites. Choose your own type of pasta for each pasta dish!

restaurant.name: Nooch
restaurant.description: Unfortunately we do not have Sushi until further notice. We apologize for the inconvenience and encourage you to try some of our other delicious foods.

restaurant.name: Ginger Restaurant
restaurant.description: Ginger is a casual little sushi joint in the East Village. Along with a wide variety of sushi and more than 30 maki rolls with funky and creative combinations (think eel, banana, and peanut butter), Ginger also serves Japanese favorites such as gyoza and miso soup.

restaurant.name: Hudson Falafel
restaurant.description: This eatery is serving up Middle Eastern favorites, from hot falafel and meat kababs to tabouli salad, humus, and honey-sweetened desserts. The wide selection of Middle Eastern dishes and snacks features many specialties; order yourself a Middle Eastern feast--or at least some tasty falafel--today!

restaurant.name: Francesco Pizzeria
restaurant.description: Try an order from Francesco Pizzeria for traditional and specialty pizzas, soup, salad, appetizers, entrees, seafood, and pasta. You can even get your pasta on a pizza with Francesco's Baked Ziti Pie, Lasagna Pie, or Penne alla Vodka Pie.

restaurant.name: Yawa Sushi
restaurant.description: A tradition sushi spot that has a large menu and provides rolls with intense layers of flavor

restaurant.name: Montes Trattoria
restaurant.description: Monte's Trattoria, a romantic Italian Restaurant located in the heart of Greenwich Village, has existed since 1918. The Mosconi family has continued its rich tradition, and Chef Pietro Mosconi delivers authentic Northen Italian dishes from his region of Emilia Romagna.

restaurant.name: Indian Taj
restaurant.description: Craving chicken tikka masala and naan? Order an Indian feast from Indian Taj, a restaurant which boasts a wide selection of common Indian favorites and more unique dishes. The menu features Indian appetizers and vegetarian, seafood, poultry, and meat entrees.

restaurant.name: Ballaro'
restaurant.description: With coffee, sandwiches, pasta, salads, and much more, Ballaro delivers fine Italian cuisine at affordable prices.

restaurant.name: Ichiban
restaurant.description: This restaurant, which is in close proximity to Penn Station, serves authentic Japanese cuisine. Ichiban serves udon and kitchen entrees as well as sushi.

restaurant.name: 28 St. Chef 28
restaurant.description: Delicious Chinese food that is fresh and best of all healthy. Indulge in your favorite Chinese staples and you won't leave feeling like a salty balloon.

restaurant.name: Tuck Shop
restaurant.description: Tuck Shop is a bakery, but of the more substantial variety: fill up on all sorts of meat pies leave satisfied.

restaurant.name: Le Caire Lounge
restaurant.landmark: Between Ave. A and Ave. B

restaurant.name: Shish Mediterranean Catering
restaurant.landmark: Vineland Ave and Tujunga Ave (Arch Drive)

restaurant.name: Whitmans
restaurant.description: Located in the heart of the East Village, this neighborhood restaurant uses locally-sourced ingredients to create classic, American slow food, including burgers, sandwiches and fresh veggies.

restaurant.name: TAJ
restaurant.description: The original East Village favorite since 1985 - Celebrating 25 years of excellence!

restaurant.name: Cherin Sushi
restaurant.description: Cherin Sushi doesn't serve any cooked food--only a wide assortment of sushi, sashimi, and hand rolls. This is especially good for fans of affordable, quality sushi.

restaurant.name: Brick Lane Curry House
restaurant.description: Brick Lane specializes in Indian food--and, of course, curries galore. They also serve many other Indian dishes, which you can eat with a side of fluffy naan and rice. Beware the infamous phaal, which is mouth-numbingly and eye-wateringly spicy.

restaurant.name: Banjara Indian Cuisine
restaurant.description: Banjara stands out with its flavorful and authentic Indian and Pakistani cuisine at affordable prices. You can get delivered to your home all sorts of entrees, pastries, chicken, rice dishes, and more. Banjara also features a lesser-known style of dish called dumpakht, in which the dish to be cooked is first covered in pastry.

restaurant.name: Wine Therapy
restaurant.description: Wine Therapy offers a wide selection of specialty and organic wines from around the world, and prides itself in offering lesser-known wines from small producers.

restaurant.name: 2nd Ave Deli
restaurant.description: A classic New York deli that gives Kosher food justice. Traditional kosher fare that could rival any Jewish grandmother's home cooked goods as well as other more modern food means that no matter how you order, you will fall in love with 2nd Ave Deli.

restaurant.name: Eileen's Cheesecake
restaurant.description: A picture may be worth a thousand words but it can't compare to the creamy taste of Eileen's delectable cheesecakes. Ordering is easy, fast, and the memory of these cakes will last. Send the perfect treat to a loved one or yourself today!$1.00 extra to write on cheesecakes
restaurant.landmark: Corner of Kenamre & Centre Opposite Lafayette & Spring

restaurant.name: Bamiyan
restaurant.description: Traditional Afghan cooking. If you're unfamiliar with Afghan flavors, Bamiyan is the place to try them. Enjoy aromatic basmati rice dishes, mild curries, charcoal-grilled kabobs, and a variety of dumplings and pasta dishes.

restaurant.name: Ruben's Empanadas
restaurant.description: A well known place for the Mexican specialty. With many varieties and an authentic recipe everyone can find something here.

restaurant.name: Positano
restaurant.description: Serving up fresh and healthy Italian cuisine in the heart of Little Italy. Zagat rated and serves homemade pasta!

restaurant.name: Kiran Indian Cuisine
restaurant.description: Kiran serves a wide variety of authentic Indian cuisine. Menu options include vegetarian as well as chicken, beef, and shrimp.

restaurant.description: Gracie's Wines features an eclectic selection of wines from across the globe at varying prices. Don't be surprised to stumble upon a hard-to-find liquor in this small wine shop!

restaurant.name: Il Cantuccio
restaurant.description: Il Cantuccio uses entirely authentic recipes when preparing their biscotti, bread, pizza, and focaccia menu items (including Italian sandwiches). With selected prime quality ingredients, careful handmade production, and the respect of the original recipes (no type of fat, preservative or food coloring is used), Il Cantuccio creates Italian specialties in the traditional fashion.

restaurant.name: Pita City Catering
restaurant.description: Believing that great health and great taste can be obtained at the same time, Pita City Falafel opened in 1996 in hopes of promoting a distinct kind of healthy cuisine to Chelsea. Pita City presents wholesome Syrian food with friendly service and atmosphere. Pita City's menu features the highest quality ingredients served family style, and the results are scrumptious.
